Pre-Game Insights: Samuel Eto’o, the president of the Cameroon Football Federation, donated 500 entry tickets to students from Saint Benoit College to attend the match between Cameroon and Kenya on October 11, 2024, at the Ahmadou Ahidjo Omnisport Stadium.
The match between Cameroon and Kenya is part of the third round of qualifying for the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations in Morocco.
Both teams share the top spot in Group J with four points each, followed by Zimbabwe with 1 point and Namibia with zero points after two matches.
The national team is counting on the support of spectators to secure victory against Kenya.
